ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. How safe or unsafe do you think it has been in this prison for male staff members who have a lot of contact with inmates?
2. How safe or unsafe do you think it has been in this prison for female staff members who have a lot of contact with inmates?
3. How safe or unsafe do you think it has been in this prison for inmates?
4. How safe do you feel you have been from being hit, punched, or assaulted by other inmates?
5. How safe do you feel your personal property has been
6. How often have there been shakedowns [searches] in your housing unit during the last six months?
Notes: 0=Never, 1=Very rarely, 2=Rarely, 3=Now and Then, 4=Often, 5=Very Often, 6=All the time, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know

ElementDescription: 7. How often have you had a strip or pat search during the past 6 months? Not including those required visits.
Notes: 0=Never, 1=Very rarely, 2=Rarely, 3=Now and Then, 4=Often, 5=Very Often, 6=All the time, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know

ElementDescription: 8. What type of housing are you assigned to?
Notes: 1=Single cell, no roommate, 2=Single cell, with 1 roommate, 3=Single cell, >2 roommates, 4=Open/partial room, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know

ElementDescription: 9. How crowded has it been in your housnig unit?
Notes: 0=Not at all crowded, 1=Slightly crowded but not uncomfortable, 2=Moderately crowded, and becoming uncomfortable, 3=More than moderately crowded, and uncomfortable, 4=Very crowded, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know

ElementDescription: 10. How noisy has it been in your housing unit during sleep hours?
Notes: 0=Not at all noisy, 1=Slightly noisy but not uncomfortable, 2=Moderately noisy, and becoming uncomfortable, 3=More than moderately noisy, and uncomfortable, 4=Very noisy, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know

ElementDescription: 11. How crowded has it been in places other than your housing unit? (for example, where you eat your meals, exercise, work, etc.)
Notes: 0=Not at all crowded, 1=Slightly crowded but not uncomfortable, 2=Moderately crowded, and becoming uncomfortable, 3=More than moderately crowded, and uncomfortable, 4=Very crowded, 7=Refused, 8=Don't Know
